NAME
	strlen_printable - give the length of a string, sans ANSI color

SYNOPSIS
	int strlen_printable(int|string str)

DESCRIPTION
	Gives the length of a string in number of characters, minus the length
	of any complete ANSI color sequences. If an integer is passed as an
	argument then 0 is returned.

	This function is not defined unless ANSI_COLOR is defined.

	If USE_UTF8 is defined, will give the length of the number of shown UTF-8
	characters, rather than number of bytes.

SEE ALSO
    terminal_colour

